<li>Phillips, R. 1980. A Comparison of Color and Visual Texture as Codes for use as Area Symbols on Relief Maps. <i>Ergonomics</i>. 23, pp. 1117–1128.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFPickles.2C_John2003">Pickles, John (2003). <i>A History of Spaces: Cartographic Reason, Mapping, and the Geo-Coded World</i>. Taylor &amp; Francis. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415144973" class="internal">ISBN 0-415-14497-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+History+of+Spaces%3A+Cartographic+Reason%2C+Mapping%2C+and+the+Geo-Coded+World&amp;rft.aulast=Pickles%2C+John&amp;rft.au=Pickles%2C+John&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=Taylor+%26+Francis&amp;rft.isbn=0-415-14497-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Rice, M., Jacobson, R., Jones. D. 2003. <i>Object Size Discrimination and Non-visual Cartographic Symbolization</i>. CA. pp. 1–12.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRobinson.2C_A.H.1953">Robinson, A.H. (1953). <i>Elements of Cartography</i>. New York: John Wiley &amp; Sons. ISBN.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Elements+of+Cartography&amp;rft.aulast=Robinson%2C+A.H.&amp;rft.au=Robinson%2C+A.H.&amp;rft.date=1953&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=John+Wiley+%26+Sons&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRobinson.2C_Arthur_H.1982">Robinson, Arthur H. (1982). <i>Early Thematic Mapping in the History of Cartography.</i>. Chicago: The University of Chicago Press..</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Early+Thematic+Mapping+in+the+History+of+Cartography.&amp;rft.aulast=Robinson%2C+Arthur+H.&amp;rft.au=Robinson%2C+Arthur+H.&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pub=The+University+of+Chicago+Press.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSircar1990">Sircar, D.C.C. (January 1990). <i>Studies in the Geography of Ancient and Medieval India</i>. Motilal Banarsidass Publishers. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8120806905" class="internal">ISBN 8120806905</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Studies+in+the+Geography+of+Ancient+and+Medieval+India&amp;rft.aulast=Sircar&amp;rft.aufirst=D.C.C.&amp;rft.au=Sircar%2C+D.C.C.&amp;rft.date=January+1990&amp;rft.pub=Motilal+Banarsidass+Publishers&amp;rft.isbn=8120806905&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSlocum.2C_T.1999">Slocum, T. (1999). <i>Thematic Cartography and Geographic Visualization</i>. Upper Saddle River, New Jersey: Prentice Hall. ISBN.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Thematic+Cartography+and+Geographic+Visualization&amp;rft.aulast=Slocum%2C+T.&amp;rft.au=Slocum%2C+T.&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.place=Upper+Saddle+River%2C+New+Jersey&amp;rft.pub=Prentice+Hall&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Sivin, Nathan (1995). <i>Science in Ancient China</i>. Brookfield, Vermont: VARIORUM, Ashgate Publishing.</li>
<li>Temple, Robert. (1986). <i>The Genius of China: 3,000 Years of Science, Discovery, and Invention</i>. With a forward by Joseph Needham. New York: Simon and Schuster, Inc. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0671620282" class="internal">ISBN 0671620282</a>.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWilford.2C_John_Noble2000">Wilford, John Noble (2000). <i>The Mapmakers</i>. Vintage Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0375708502" class="internal">ISBN 0-375-70850-2</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mapmakers&amp;rft.aulast=Wilford%2C+John+Noble&amp;rft.au=Wilford%2C+John+Noble&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.pub=Vintage+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0-375-70850-2&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:History_of_cartography"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Woodward, David, ed. (2007) <i>Cartography in the European Renaissance</i>. Volume 3 of <i>The History of Cartography</i>. Chicago and London: University of Chicago Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0226907333" class="internal">ISBN 0-226-90733-3</a>.</li>
<li>Wright, David Curtis (2001) <i>The History of China</i>. Westport: Greenwood Press.</li>
</ul>
